Cluster Login with management IP address:

	Note: Node management cannot failover but cluster management IP will failover to any node to log in.
	
	
	1. Create Aggregate/Tier :
	Storage Recommendation: Share all disks to 2 nodes by default.

	2. After creating an aggregate we see 2 types of aggregate
	>> Storage aggregate show
	The name starts with "aggr0_Cluster1_01" and "aggr0_cluster1_02"  ----> These are root aggregates
	The name starts with "aggr1_cluster1_01" and "aggr1_cluster1_02" ------> Data Aggregates.
	
	Root Aggregate: Used by a particular node to store the OS and other config files.
	Data Aggregate: to create the volumes and store the data
	
		a. Regular aggregates: Only HDD
		b. Flash Pool: SSDs are used for flash cache 
		c. Flash: Only SSDs aggregated
		d. Fabric Pool: Aggregate is connected to the cloud storage
	
	
	>> Storage aggregate show -aggregate <aggregate_name>
	>> Storage aggregate show -aggregate <aggregate_name> -fields maxraidsize
	
	Aggregate: Aggregate is a collection of raid groups or disks with raid applied.
		****	The max raid size is 24 disks ****
			It will create 2 RAID groups if you have 2 RAIDs   48 disks
			
			
	For root aggregate min 3 disks to create aggregate with RAID DP.
	For data aggregate, we need a minimum of 5 disks.
	
	Capacity calculations:
	======================
	The market disk capacity is 2 TB.
	When installing the disk we see only 1.8 TB is usable space.
	
	RAID 4: Dedicated parity disk, 1 disk failure
	RAID DP: Dedicated parity disk, 2 disk failure
	RAID Tec: Dedicated parity disk, 3 disk failure
	RAID 5 & 6: Distributed parity Disk
	
	RAID DP used 2 dedicated parity disks (Out of 20 disks, 2 for parity and 18 for data)
	18*1.8 = 32.4 TB
	
	WAFL: 
	Write Anywhere File Layout
The Write Anywhere File Layout is a proprietary file system that supports large, high-performance RAID arrays, quick restarts without lengthy consistency checks in the event of a crash or power failure, and growing the filesystems size quickly

	
	WAFL takes 10% space in each disk 
	So usable is 32.4 - 3.24 = 29.16 TB usable.
	
	WAFL is the heart of ONTAP
	NAS - File system
	SAN - LUN as hard disk
	
	ONTAP divides each disk into 4 KB Blocks
	Each block has its ID/index
	An index is stored by WAFL

		
		

		
			
			
	
	
	
	
	
	

